('Rigel', 'HR 1713', 24436, 'β Ori', 60, 'From an abbrevation of its ind-A (and sci-A) name rijl al-jauza\', the Foot of al-jauza\'.\" \"Rigel\" is one of the oldest Arabic star names applied in the West, from the end of the 10th century A.D.', 'Arabic', 'Kunitzsch, Paul; Smart, Tim (2006). A Dictionary of Modern star Names: A Short Guide to 254 Star Names and Their Derivations (2nd rev. ed.). Cambridge, Massachusetts: Sky Pub.', 'Ori', '2016/06/30', 365),
